cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses generative neural network models and proposes a new methodology to assess and measure the distribution of a generative model. It also compares different types of generative models based on their performance on a real-world dataset. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as generative models are often used in image generation and manipulation tasks. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as generative models are a popular area of research in AI. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category as the paper specifically discusses neural network models. 

Finally, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a relevant sub-category as the paper proposes a new methodology for comparing distributions using persistent homology.
